Release Notes

  The Rio team would like to announce the release of Rio 4.1.

  Rio 4.1 is {{{./download.html}download}}

* 4.1 Release Notes

 The full list of changes can be found in our {{{http://jira.rio-project.org}issue management system}}, and is reproduced below.
    
** Bug

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-239}RIO-239}} - Syntax diagram for resources, artifact and association management incorrect

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-242}RIO-242}} - NPE in Utilization strategy when logging set to FINEST

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-244}RIO-244}} - If groovy configuration has a MissPropertyException script error, throw ConfigurationException with cause of MissPropertyException

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-266}RIO-266}} - Resolver returns wrong snapshot artifact name

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-268}RIO-268}} - DSL missing support for locators

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-272}RIO-272}} - Unable to reload service that has a groovy configuration

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-275}RIO-275}} - Provide better management of PermGen

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-277}RIO-277}} - AssociationDescripor.setLocators() javadoc misleading

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-278}RIO-278}} - Rio Mojos should avoid being executed if they are not the root project

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-280}RIO-280}} - Make sure oar is installed as a .oar when packaging type is not "oar"

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-283}RIO-283}} - Resolver fails to replace ${pom.groupId} if part of a groupId declaration

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-284}RIO-284}} - Maven modules need unique name to support development in Eclipse

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-285}RIO-285}} - Rio deploy, undeploy and ui mojos do not provide support for setting groups

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-287}RIO-287}} - POJO has createProxy called before setConfiguration

     []
    
** Improvement

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-237}RIO-237}} - Refactor AssociationManagement

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-238}RIO-238}} - Example should declare dependencyManagement for Rio version

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-245}RIO-245}} - Forked services should use a rolling FileHandler for logs

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-246}RIO-246}} - Remove need for thread pool configuration in Cybernode

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-257}RIO-257}} - Simplify Watchable and WatchRegistry

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-259}RIO-259}} - StaticCybernode should not require RIO_HOME to be set

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-263}RIO-263}} - Check if RIO_NATIVE_DIR is already set before processing it in rio script

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-276}RIO-276}} - Add lifecycle annotations

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-293}RIO-293}} - Add hotspot options for out of memory behavior

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-294}RIO-294}} - Provide ability for Resolver to include Rio platform when generating classpath


     []
    
**  New Feature

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-234}RIO-234}} - Add Drools as a way to provide declarative policy enforcement for SLAs

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-236}RIO-236}} - Use of Futures with Associations

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-247}RIO-247}} - Log Handler that recognizes exceptions and sends remote events

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-248}RIO-248}} - Rio UI should allow jconsole to be attached to forked service

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-258}RIO-258}} - Add version numbers to ServiceInfo

     * {{{http://jira.rio-project.org/browse/RIO-270}RIO-270}} - Add a method to the Cybernode interface for querying its enlistment state.

     []
    
